An 18-year-old student, Pekka-Eric Auvinen, carried out a shooting at Jokela High School in Tuusula, Finland, killing eight people before taking his own life.
This tragic event marked the first school shooting in Finland since 1989.
Auvinen, known for his radical beliefs, posted videos online praising past school shooters.
The incident shocked the nation, prompting condolences from Prime Minister Matti Vanhanen.
Flags flew at half-mast as Finland mourned the victims, including the school principal and nurse.
